Order

The petitioner (Mujahid), being arrayed as an accused in case F.I.R. No. 958/2024, dated 08.08.2024, registered with Police Station City Phoolnagar, District Kasur, for offences under Sections 395, 412 and 109 of PPC, seek his post arrest bail, after the same was refused by the Court of learned Additional Sessions Judge, Pattoki, vide order dated 19.03.2025.

2.       After hearing learned counsel for the petitioner, learned counsel for complainant, learned Deputy Prosecutor General and perusal of record, it was observed that according to F.I.R. on 07.08.2024 at about 07:15 P.M. some unknown persons broke into the jewellary shop of Shabbir Hussain (complainant) and deprived him of golden jewellary weighing 3 Kg, silver jewellary 4 Kg and cash of
Rs. 30,00,000/-.

3.       Record speaks that occurrence took place on 07.08.2024, for which F.L.R. was got registered on 08.08.2024, wherein no body was named as culprit and it was claimed that unknown culprits, who committed the robbery, could be identified, if seen again. Petitioner was introduced in a supplementary statement got recorded by complainant without disclosing any source of information. Surprizingly petitioner was not put to identification parade, which fact alone was sufficient to make present case that one of further inquiry. Recovery of cash of Rs. 600,000/-shown on the pointing out of petitioner could be scrutinized during the trial. All the above said facts, when taken into consideration accumulatively, were sufficient to make the present case that one of further inquiry. In such like cases bail was rule, whereas its refusal was an exception. I, therefore, think it appropriate to exercise my discretion in favour of the petitioner.

4.       For what has been discussed above, the present petition succeeds. Petitioner is ordered to be released on bail subject to his furnishing bail bonds in the sum of Rs. 200,000/- with one surety in the like amount to the satisfaction of learned trial Court.

5.       Needless to mention that any observation made in the above order is tentative in nature and shall not influence the learned trial Court in any manner.

