[12/30/25, 3:48:12 PM] ~ insaf sab k liey: Some misunderstanding in law prevails that Court can take judicial notice of only those facts which are listed in Article 112 of Qanun-eShahadat Order 1984, and of course newspaper or journal is not mentioned in such Article. Suffice it to say that such Article says that “Facts of which Court must take judicial notice” the word “must” make it obligatory for the Court to take judicial notice of all such facts listed in Article 112 ibid without asking for a formal proof. Whereas Article 111 ibid gives a discretion to the Court to take judicial notice of any fact not listed in Article 112 ibid, depending upon the circumstances of the case. Thus, Court can take judicial notice of a news clipping subject to the considerations that its admissibility depends on several factors, including the relevance to the case, the authenticity of the clipping, and whether the court deems it reliable. 
