d so, but it cannot pass a sentence against him---Trial Court must forward the proceedings to the High Court to pass such orders as the High Court think fit---Unless the accused is insane, the Trial Court can proceed with the trial even though the accused cannot understand the proceedings---Given the circumstances, the Trial Court submitted a reference without complying with the spirit provided under S. 341, Cr.P.C.---Therefore, the matter was remanded to the trial Court to proceed as per the law
